    {
      "number": 9,
      "id": "I_kwDOHK26QM5UimqV",
      "title": "Add another mitigation? Only display QR Codes in an authenticated session on the original device",
      "url": "https://github.com/oauth-wg/oauth-cross-device-security/issues/9",
      "state": "CLOSED",
      "author": "damienbod",
      "authorAssociation": "CONTRIBUTOR",
      "assignees": [],
      "labels": [],
      "body": "## Only display QR Codes in an authenticated session on the original device\r\n\r\n## Use Case\r\n\r\nI want to use my E-ID on a verifier website to prove my identity. If I authenticated on the correct website using a phishing resistant authentication and only after this, can I scan the QR Code to present my verifiable credentials presentation. This works good, as a lot of the website where I require a digital identity check, I already have an account and can use a phishing resistant authentication first.\r\n\r\nI could add a text for this, if you think this is a good idea.\r\n\r\nGreetings Damien\r\n",
      "createdAt": "2022-10-21T13:37:53Z",
      "updatedAt": "2022-11-04T14:56:21Z",
      "closedAt": "2022-11-04T14:56:21Z",
      "comments": [
        {
          "author": "PieterKas",
          "authorAssociation": "COLLABORATOR",
          "body": "@damienbod I think of this as a type of \"authenticated flow\" where the user authenticated the channel before engaging in an additional cross device flow. I think it is a reasonable mitigation, would you like to take a stab at writing up a more detailed description of the attack?",
          "createdAt": "2022-10-27T15:41:51Z",
          "updatedAt": "2022-10-27T15:41:51Z"
        },
        {
          "author": "damienbod",
          "authorAssociation": "CONTRIBUTOR",
          "body": "@PieterKas Thanks for the feedback. I created a PR for this:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/oauthstuff/draft-cross-device-security/pull/19\r\n\r\nGreetings Damien",
          "createdAt": "2022-10-28T10:47:03Z",
          "updatedAt": "2022-10-28T10:47:03Z"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
