    {
      "number": 11,
      "id": "I_kwDOHK26QM5U4CZR",
      "title": "Update section on CIBA",
      "url": "https://github.com/oauth-wg/oauth-cross-device-security/issues/11",
      "state": "CLOSED",
      "author": "PieterKas",
      "authorAssociation": "COLLABORATOR",
      "assignees": [],
      "labels": [],
      "body": "From Brian Campbell: https://mailarchive.ietf.org/arch/msg/oauth/G9Q6_NkLS4-dglXH1ztxaIZgi_w/\r\n\r\nJust want to try and clarify some things about the status of CIBA, which is\r\ndescribed somewhat erroneously as a \"standard under development.\"  There is\r\na FAPI profile of CIBA that is still under development but core CIBA\r\n<https://openid.net/specs/openid-client-initiated-backchannel-authentication-core-1_0.html>\r\nwas finalized last year.",
      "createdAt": "2022-10-26T12:56:10Z",
      "updatedAt": "2022-10-27T15:36:27Z",
      "closedAt": "2022-10-27T15:36:27Z",
      "comments": []
    },
    {
      "number": 12,
      "id": "I_kwDOHK26QM5U4DMu",
      "title": "Provide guidance to not use cross device protocols for same device scenarios",
      "url": "https://github.com/oauth-wg/oauth-cross-device-security/issues/12",
      "state": "CLOSED",
      "author": "PieterKas",
      "authorAssociation": "COLLABORATOR",
      "assignees": [],
      "labels": [],
      "body": "From Joseph Heenan: https://mailarchive.ietf.org/arch/msg/oauth/KVp_Zc03vxvfDS_-R1ybDKiSXKk/\r\n\r\nI may have missed it, but it may be worth being move explicit that one solution is to avoid using cross-device flows for same-device scenarios? It\u2019s sort of obvious, but questions like \u201cwell CIBA works for both cross-device and same-device, can\u2019t I save myself effort by only implementing CIBA and not bothering with standard redirect-based OAuth flows?\u201d are commonly asked.",
      "createdAt": "2022-10-26T12:58:34Z",
      "updatedAt": "2022-10-27T15:19:43Z",
      "closedAt": "2022-10-27T15:19:43Z",
      "comments": []
    },
    {
      "number": 13,
      "id": "I_kwDOHK26QM5U4DhX",
      "title": "Clarify push notifications for CIBA",
      "url": "https://github.com/oauth-wg/oauth-cross-device-security/issues/13",
      "state": "CLOSED",
      "author": "PieterKas",
      "authorAssociation": "COLLABORATOR",
      "assignees": [],
      "labels": [],
      "body": "From Joseph Heenan: https://mailarchive.ietf.org/arch/msg/oauth/KVp_Zc03vxvfDS_-R1ybDKiSXKk/\r\n\r\n\"If FIDO2/WebAuthn support is not available, Channel Initiated Backchannel Authentication (CIBA) provides an alternative, provided that the underlying devices can receive push notifications.\u201d\r\n\r\nIt might be best to use a term other than \u2018push notifications\u2019 there or otherwise rewording this, as there are alternatives. e.g. I think there\u2019s at least one CIBA implementation out there that can use email to notify the user of an authorization request.\r\n",
      "createdAt": "2022-10-26T12:59:30Z",
      "updatedAt": "2022-10-27T15:30:48Z",
      "closedAt": "2022-10-27T15:30:48Z",
      "comments": []
    },
    {
      "number": 17,
      "id": "I_kwDOHK26QM5U_Cm5",
      "title": "Correct Typo \"Channel Initiated\" -> \"Client Initiated\"",
      "url": "https://github.com/oauth-wg/oauth-cross-device-security/issues/17",
      "state": "CLOSED",
      "author": "PieterKas",
      "authorAssociation": "COLLABORATOR",
      "assignees": [],
      "labels": [],
      "body": "From: https://mailarchive.ietf.org/arch/msg/oauth/ghOa788f-KfLoI8tTzrgWP8rWSA/\r\n\r\nAs an editorial note, the text referenced (section 5.2.4) by Joseph, \"If\r\nFIDO2/WebAuthn support is not available, Channel Initiated Backchannel\r\nAuthentication (CIBA) provides an alternative..\" should reference \"Client\r\nInitiated Backchannel Authentication (CIBA)\". This reference is correct in\r\nthe other sections of the document.\r\n\r\nBR,\r\nBjorn",
      "createdAt": "2022-10-27T15:12:30Z",
      "updatedAt": "2022-10-27T15:32:24Z",
      "closedAt": "2022-10-27T15:32:07Z",
      "comments": [
