          "createdAt": "2022-10-27T15:32:23Z",
          "updatedAt": "2022-10-27T15:32:23Z"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "number": 18,
      "id": "I_kwDOHK26QM5VDr-6",
      "title": "Add \"Detect and Terminate\" as a practical mitigations",
      "url": "https://github.com/oauth-wg/oauth-cross-device-security/issues/18",
      "state": "CLOSED",
      "author": "PieterKas",
      "authorAssociation": "COLLABORATOR",
      "assignees": [],
      "labels": [],
      "body": "It is possible to detect the same user codes being redeemed, which is likely to signifiy an attack in progress. Adding these codes toa  deny list and then terminating all sessions assositted with the tokens issued (e.g. via someithing like SSE/CAEP) to the user as a result of redeeming that specific user code stops further attacks and remediates the existing attack",
      "createdAt": "2022-10-28T10:11:56Z",
      "updatedAt": "2022-11-04T20:45:38Z",
      "closedAt": "2022-11-04T20:45:38Z",
      "comments": [
        {
          "author": "PieterKas",
          "authorAssociation": "COLLABORATOR",
          "body": "Added Detect and remediate section",
          "createdAt": "2022-11-04T20:45:37Z",
          "updatedAt": "2022-11-04T20:45:37Z"
        }
      ]
    },
