    {
      "number": 26,
      "id": "I_kwDOHK26QM5WU5zk",
      "title": "Clarify when cross device flows should be used on same device scenarios",
      "url": "https://github.com/oauth-wg/oauth-cross-device-security/issues/26",
      "state": "CLOSED",
      "author": "PieterKas",
      "authorAssociation": "COLLABORATOR",
      "assignees": [],
      "labels": [],
      "body": "From discussion with Kristina Yasuda\r\n\r\n[openid / connect / Pull Request #327: clarified the definition of response mode post - Issue #1626 \u2014 Bitbucket](https://bitbucket.org/openid/connect/pull-requests/327)\r\n\r\nif the same protocol allows for both same and cross device flows and there are legitimate reasons to use cross for same, same cross device protections shuold apply to same d flow\r\n\r\nif a protocol allows only for cross d, use another same d protocol",
      "createdAt": "2022-11-14T15:55:54Z",
      "updatedAt": "2022-11-14T22:44:26Z",
